.modal.ng-cloak#info_modal
  .modal-dialog(ng-click='$event.stopPropagation()')
    .modal-content
      //- .modal-header
      .modal-body
        button.close(type='button' ng-click='$parent.$parent.modalTemplate = false') Ã—
        h3 About
        span(ng-include='"./includes/about_snippet.html"')

        
        hr
        h4 Workflow guide
        ol

          li Load a fresh spritesheet using the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-folder-open
            |  &nbsp;New button

          li Add and name a new sprite 
            code eg "mario"

          li Add and name a new action 
            code eg "stand"

          li Add a new frame (shortcut: 
            kbd f
            |  )

          li Set your view area
            ul
              li Scroll and click/drag on the small canvas to set the view area

          li Set frame coordinates
            ul
              li Left click/drag on the large canvas to set the top left frame coordinates
              li Right click/drag on the large canvas to set the bottom right frame coordinates
          
          li Save your work with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-floppy-disk
            | &nbsp;Save button

          li Copy the resulting JSON from the  
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-circle-arrow-down
            | &nbsp;Output area into your project

        hr
        h4 Good to know
        ul
          li Change the JSON output fomat in the options dialog (the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-cog
            |  button)

          li Load and delete saved spritesheets with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-open
            | &nbsp;Load dialog

          li Update your current spritesheet with the 
            span.glyphicon.glyphicon-repeat
            | &nbsp;Update button. For browser security reasons you'll need to point the app to your spritesheet at least once each time you start the application, but don't worry. It's easy.
        hr
        .alert.alert-info
          | Because SpriteBreaker makes use of the latest web standards, people using older browsers may run into problems. Then again, I'm not really sure why anyone with an outdated browser would be using this.


      .modal-footer
        button.btn.btn-default(type='button' ng-click='$parent.$parent.modalTemplate = false') Close
